            <!-- Slide 4: What is PBDCL? -->
            <div class="slide" id="slide4">
                <div class="slide-header">
                    <h1 class="slide-title">What is Problem-Based Digital Context Learning (PBDCL)?</h1>
                    <div class="slide-number">4/16</div>
                </div>
                <div class="slide-content">
                    <div class="content-card">
                        <h2 class="card-title"><i class="fas fa-book"></i> Definition</h2>
                        <p>A student-centered approach where learners engage with realistic, contextualized problems in a digital environment like simulations, virtual patients, and online platforms, to develop clinical reasoning and knowledge.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Slide 5: Key Principles -->
            <div class="slide" id="slide5">
                <div class="slide-header">
                    <h1 class="slide-title">Key Principles of PBDCL</h1>
                    <div class="slide-number">5/16</div>
                </div>
                <div class="slide-content">
                    <div class="principle-card">
                        <span class="principle-number">1</span>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Problem as the Starting Point:</strong> Learning begins with a compelling clinical scenario
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="principle-card">
                        <span class="principle-number">2</span>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Student-Centered Learning:</strong> The tutor is a facilitator; students drive their own learning
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="principle-card">
                        <span class="principle-number">3</span>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Digital Immersion:</strong> Uses technology (VR, e-learning modules, video) to simulate reality
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="principle-card">
                        <span class="principle-number">4</span>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Collaboration in teams:</strong> Students work in teams, mirroring interdisciplinary healthcare
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="principle-card">
                        <span class="principle-number">5</span>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Reflection and critical analysis:</strong> Critical analysis of the learning process and outcomes is essential
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Slide 6: The PBDCL Process -->
            <div class="slide" id="slide6">
                <div class="slide-header">
                    <h1 class="slide-title">The PBDCL Process</h1>
                    <div class="slide-number">6/16</div>
                </div>
                <div class="slide-content">
                    <div class="process-step">
                        <div class="step-number">1</div>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Present Problem:</strong> Introduce a digital clinical scenario
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="process-step">
                        <div class="step-number">2</div>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Identify Knowledge Gaps:</strong> What do we need to know to solve this?
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="process-step">
                        <div class="step-number">3</div>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Self-Directed Learning:</strong> Research using digital resources
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="process-step">
                        <div class="step-number">4</div>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Collaborate & Synthesize:</strong> Discuss findings and apply them to the problem
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="process-step">
                        <div class="step-number">5</div>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Present Solution & Reflect:</strong> Propose an intervention and reflect on the process
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Slide 7: Benefits -->
            <div class="slide" id="slide7">
